HEADWORD: Japonica
<hw>Ja*pon"i*ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., Japanese,
fr. <ets>Japonia</ets> Japan.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A species of
Camellia (<spn>Camellia Japonica</spn>), a native of Japan, bearing
beautiful red or white flowers. Many other genera have species of the
same name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

